Recently, U.S. Representative Marjorie Taylor Greene compared the billions of dollars that the U.S. Congress is rushing to send to Ukraine for humanitarian and military aid to a "money laundering scheme". She accused the U.S. of hypocrisy of its aid to Ukraine, and queried the ultimate direction of the huge amount of money. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michelle Van den Bergh looks into who finally gets money, as the humanitarian aid for Ukraine exposes the corruption of Washington.